header.gameNote: CONTINENTAL TIRE LAS VEGAS CLASSIC AT LAS VEGAS

article.headline: Portland 57, Bradley 55
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Ryan Nicholas and Derrick Rodgers scored 12 points apiece to lead Portland to a 57-55 win over Bradley in the consolation game of the Las Vegas Classic on Sunday night. Nicholas also grabbed 12 rebounds for a double-double. Rodgers was 4 of 5 from the field. Oskars Reinfelds added 10 points. Riley Barker grabbed 10 rebounds. Portland led 28-27 at halftime in a game with 17 lead changes. Bradley had another chance to win the game, but Will Egolf missed a 3-pointer at the buzzer. Portland (7-7) shot 44 percent from the field for the game, while Bradley (8-4) shot 31.5 percent. Portland had 42 rebounds, while Bradley had 31. Dyricus Simms-Edwards led Bradley with 15 points. Egolf and Walt Lemon Jr. had 10 points apiece. Jake Eastman had six rebounds before fouling out.
